HEADWORD: Hesperetin
<hw>Hes*per"e*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A white, crystalline substance having a sweetish taste, obtained by
the decomposition of hesperidin, and regarded as a complex derivative of
caffeic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hesperian</ent>⟦br⟧
